Tests for normality

Non-Parametric Analyses

Bar Graph: Median by Test Trial

There was no difference in looking times between the first Contact test event (Median = 14.1) and the first No Contact event (Median = 15.05), (Wilcoxon Z = -0.21, p = 0.83)

There was no difference in looking times between the second Contact test event (Median = 10.4) and the second No Contact event (Median = 11.8), (Wilcoxon Z = -0.11, p = 0.91).

There was no difference in looking times between the third Contact test event (Median = 10.45) and the third No Contact event (Median = 13.25), (Wilcoxon Z = -1.2, p = 0.23).

Bar Graph: Median by Test Trial (Younger infants)

For younger infants, there was no difference in looking times between the first Contact test event (Median = 13.7) and the first No Contact event (Median = 14.3), (Wilcoxon Z = -0.49, p = 0.63)

For younger infants, there was no difference in looking times between the second Contact test event (Median = 12.1) and the second No Contact event (Median = 13.4), (Wilcoxon Z = -0.45, p = 0.65).

For younger infants, there was no difference in looking times between the third Contact test event (Median = 13) and the third No Contact event (Median = 13.3), (Wilcoxon Z = 0, p = 1).

Bar Graph: Median by Test Trial (Older infants)

There was no difference in looking times between the first Contact test event (Median = 14.4) and the first No Contact event (Median = 16.2), (Wilcoxon Z = -0.08, p = 0.94)

There was no difference in looking times between the second Contact test event (Median = 8.7) and the second No Contact event (Median = 10.5), (Wilcoxon Z = -0.17, p = 0.86).

There was no difference in looking times between the third Contact test event (Median = 8.3) and the third No Contact event (Median = 13.2), (Wilcoxon Z = -1.75, p = 0.08).

Parametric Analyses

Bar Graph: Means by Test Trial (All infants)

There was no difference in looking times between the first Possible test event (M = 18.83) and the first Impossible event (M = 18.75), (t(49) = -0.03, p = 0.97).

There was no difference in looking times between the second Possible test event (M = 15.24) and the second Impossible event (M = 14.38), (t(49) = -0.38, p = 0.7).

There was no difference in looking times between the third Possible test event (M = 15.04) and the third Impossible event (M = 17.1), (t(49) = 0.84, p = 0.41).

Bar Graph: Means by Test Trial (Younger infants)

For infants younger than 7.28 months, there was no difference in looking times between the first Possible test event (M = 16.67) and the first Impossible event (M = 17.61), (t(24) = 0.27, p = 0.79).

For infants younger than 7.28 months, there was no difference in looking times between the second Possible test event (M = 15.85) and the second Impossible event (M = 13.98), (t(24) = -0.63, p = 0.54).

For infants younger than 7.28 months, there was no difference in looking times between the third Possible test event (M = 19.32) and the third Impossible event (M = 16.54), (t(24) = -0.81, p = 0.43).

Bar Graph: Means by Test Trial (Older infants)

For infants older than 7.28 months, there was no difference in looking times between the first Possible test event (M = 20.98) and the first Impossible event (M = 19.88), (t(24) = -0.31, p = 0.76).

For infants older than 7.28 months, there was no difference in looking times between the second Possible test event (M = 14.64) and the second Impossible event (M = 14.78), (t(24) = 0.04, p = 0.97).

For infants older than 7.28 months, there was no difference in looking times between the third Possible test event (M = 10.76) and the third Impossible event (M = 17.66), (t(24) = 2.06, p = 0.05).

Bar Graph: Average Looking Time Across Condition

There was no difference in looking times between the average looking time of all three Possible test events (M = 16.37) and the average looking time of all three Impossible events (M = 16.74), (t(49) = -0.25, p = 0.81).

Between-Subject Analyses

Bar Graph: Medians of first trial (Between-Subject)

There was no difference in looking times between the first Contact test event (Median = 14.6) and the first No Contact event (Median = 14.9) between subjects, (Wilcoxon Z = -0.47, p = 0.64)

Bar Graph: Means of first trial (Between-Subject)

There was no difference in looking times between the first Possible test event (M = 23.84) and the first Impossible event (M = 18.02) between subjects, (t(43.45) = -1.21, p = 0.23).

Dishabituation Analyses

(Difference between last familiarization and first test)

Positive values indicate dishabituation (renewed interest), negative values indicate no dishabituation

Bar Graph: Median of Dishabituation

There was no difference in dishabituation to the first Contact test event (Median = 0) and dishabituation to the first No Contact event (Median = -0.1), (Wilcoxon Z = -1.15, p = 0.25)

Bar Graph: Mean of dishabituation

There was no difference in dishabituation to the first Possible test event (M = 5.5) and dishabituation to the first Impossible event (M = -3.49), (t(43.72) = -1.84, p = 0.07).
